{"id": 3079, "source": "pestle", "subject": "physics", "course": null, "level": "SL", "paper": "1", "year": "2021", "session": "21M", "subtopic": "6-1-circular-motion", "title": "21M.1.SL.TZ2.23", "topic_id": "6", "source_url": "https://pestle.pages.dev/app/", "question_html": "<div class=\"question\">\n<p>An object moves in a circle of constant radius. Values of the centripetal force <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>F</mi></math> are measured for different values of angular velocity <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>ω</mi></math>. A graph is plotted with <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>ω</mi></math> on the <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math>-axis. Which quantity plotted on the <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi></math>-axis will produce a straight-line graph?</p>\n<p>A.  <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msqrt><mi>F</mi></msqrt></math></p>\n<p>B.  <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>F</mi></math></p>\n<p>C.  <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>F</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></math></p>\n<p>D.  <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mi>F</mi></mfrac></math></p>\n</div>", "solution_html": "<div class=\"question\">\n<p>A</p>\n</div>", "examiners_html": "<div class=\"question\">\n[N/A]\n</div>"}